OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F435A1784576903
OL,3,CSchoolboy acquitted of attempted
OL,4,Cmurder after stabbing teacher in head
OL,6,FShe said "alarm bells" began to ring
OL,7,Fin her head when he shut the door to
OL,8,Fthe classroom, saying it was cold.
OL,10,FThe jury was told the student then
OL,11,Fpulled a large kitchen knife from his
OL,12,Fbag, striking her in the head.
OL,14,FThe court heard that a "violent
OL,15,Fstruggle" ensued in which Mrs Williams
OL,16,Ftried to take the knife from him
OL,17,Fbefore he ran from the school.
OL,26,@nD@JOUnD@VO]vD@XOUwD@IO]
