CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F435A1784576903
OL,3,CSchoolboy acquitted of attempted
OL,4,Cmurder after stabbing teacher in head
OL,6,FThe jury was shown CCTV of the
OL,7,Fteenager leaving the school premises,
OL,8,Fbefore he went to his grandmother's
OL,9,Fhome, telling her: "Something went in
OL,10,Fmy head, nan."
OL,12,FChristopher Rees KC, prosecuting, said
OL,13,Fin his closing speech last week: "He
OL,14,Fknows the truth about what he did, he
OL,15,Fjust doesn't have, I'm afraid, the
OL,16,Fcourage or the remorse to tell anyone
OL,17,Fabout it.
OL,19,F"He brought the knife into school
OL,20,Fbecause he planned to attack the
OL,21,Fteacher.
OL,26,@qD@TOUrD@NO]uD@bOU{D@AOU
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G6/8
